obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (38228)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38228&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Institute of Petroleum and`
  line `Energy Act, 2017.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 22nd January, 2018, vide notification No. S.O. 272(E), dated 17th January, 2018, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (38272)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of Indian Institute of Petroleum and Energy as an institution of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38272&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whereas the objects of the institution known as the Indian Institute of Petroleum and`
  line `Energy, Vishakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh are such as to make the institution one of national`
  line `importance, it is hereby declared that the institution known as the Indian Institute of Petroleum and`
  line `Energy is an institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (38230)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38230&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date appointed under sub-section (2) of section 1 for coming`
  line `into force of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Board of Governors of the Institute constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the General Council;`
  line
  line `(d) "Director" means the Director of the Institute appointed under section 20;`
  line
  line `(e) "fund" means the fund of the Institute to be maintained under section 24;`
  line
  line `(f) "General Council" means the General Council constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(g) "Institute" means the Indian Institute of Petroleum and Energy incorporated under section 4;`
  line
  line `(h) "President" means the President of the Board appointed under clause (a) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 5;`
  line
  line `(i) "Registrar" means the Registrar of the Institute referred to in section 21;`
  line
  line `(j) "Senate" means the Senate of the Institute referred to in section 17;`
  line
  line `(k) "Society" means the Indian Institute of Petroleum and Energy Society, Vishakhapatnam,`
  line `Andhra Pradesh registered under the Andhra Pradesh Societies Registration Act, 2001 (Andhra`
  line `Pradesh Act 35 of 2001); and`
  line
  line `(l) "Statutes" and "Ordinances" mean, respectively, the Statutes and the Ordinances of the`
  line `Institute made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (38231)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Incorporation of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38231&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Indian Institute of Petroleum and Energy, Vishakhapatnam,`
  line `Andhra Pradesh, an institution registered under the Andhra Pradesh Societies Registration Act, 2001,`
  line `shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal with power, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract, and shall, by that`
  line `name, sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (38232)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of Board of Governors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38232&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be constituted by the`
  line `Central Government for the purposes of this Act, a Board to be known as the Board of Governors`
  line `consisting of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the President to be appointed by the Central Government in such manner as may be`
  line `provided by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first President shall be appointed by the Central Government on such terms and`
  line `conditions as it deems fit, for a period not exceeding six months from the date the first Statutes comes`
  line `into force;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director of the Institute, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) two persons from the Board of Directors of the promoting companies to be nominated by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this clause, promoting companies mean those companies`
  line `contributing to the endowment fund referred to in section 25;`
  line
  line `(d) one Professor of the Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore to be nominated by the Director`
  line `of that Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) five eminent experts in the field of petroleum technology, renewable and non-renewable energy`
  line `covering the entire hydrocarbon value chain having specialised knowledge or operational experience`
  line `in respect of education, research, engineering and technology to be nominated by the General`
  line `Council, in consultation with the Director of the Institute;`
  line
  line `( f) two Professors of the Institute to be nominated by the Senate of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(g) one representative of the graduates of the Institute to be nominated by the Executive`
  line `Committee of the Alumni Association.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar of the Institute shall act as the Secretary of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall ordinarily meet four times during a calendar year.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (38233)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office of, vacancies among, and allowances payable to, members of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38233&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this section, the term of office of the President or any other member of`
  line `the Board, other than ex officio members, shall be three years from the date of his appointment or`
  line `nomination thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) An ex officio member shall cease to be a member of the Board as soon as he vacates the office`
  line `by virtue of which he is a member of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of a member nominated to fill a casual vacancy shall continue for the remainder of`
  line `the term of the member in whose place he has been nominated.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, an outgoing member shall, unless the`
  line `Central Government otherwise directs, continue in office until another person is nominated as a`
  line `member in his place.`
  line
  line `(5) The members of the Board shall be entitled to such allowances, if any, from the Institute, as`
  line `may be provided for in the Statutes, but no member other than the member referred to in clause (f) of`
  line `section 5 shall be entitled to any salary.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (38234)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Vesting of properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38234&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day and subject to the other provisions of`
  line `this Act, all properties which had vested in the Society immediately before that day, shall, on and`
  line `from that day, vest in the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (38235)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Effect of incorporation of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38235&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to the Society in any contract or other instrument shall be deemed as a`
  line `reference to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) all the rights and liabilities of the Society shall be transferred to, and be the rights and`
  line `liabilities of, the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38236)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Functions of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38236&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) nurture and promote quality and excellence in education and research in the area of`
  line `petroleum and hydrocarbons and energy;`
  line
  line `(ii) provide for programmes and courses of instruction and research leading to the award of the`
  line `Bachelors, Masters and Doctoral degrees in engineering and technology, management, sciences`
  line `and arts in the area of petroleum and hydrocarbons and energy;`
  line
  line `(iii) grant, subject to such conditions as the Institute may determine, degrees, diplomas, certificates`
  line `or other academic distinctions or titles at various academic levels to candidates who have attained the`
  line `prescribed standard of proficiency as judged on the basis of examination or on any other basis of`
  line `testing and evaluation and to withdraw any such degrees, diplomas, certificates or other academic`
  line `distinctions or titles for good and sufficient reasons;`
  line
  line `(iv) confer honorary degrees or other distinctions and to institute and award fellowships,`
  line `scholarships, exhibitions, prizes and medals;`
  line
  line `(v) lay down standards of admission to the Institute through an examination or any other`
  line `method of testing and evaluation;`
  line
  line `(vi) manage the content, quality, design and continuous evaluation of its academic and research`
  line `programmes in a manner that earns accreditation of an international stature;`
  line
  line `(vii) promote research and development for the benefit of oil, gas and petrochemical industry`
  line `and the energy sector through the integration of teaching and research;`
  line
  line `(viii) foster close educational and research interaction through networking with national,`
  line `regional and international players in the oil, gas and petrochemical industry and the energy sector;`
  line
  line `(ix) co-operate with educational and research institutions in any part of the world having objects`
  line `wholly or partly similar to those of the Institute by exchange of teachers and scholars, conduct of`
  line `joint research, undertaking sponsored research and consultancy projects, etc;`
  line
  line `(x) organise national and international symposia, seminars and conferences in the area of`
  line `petroleum and hydrocarbons and energy;`
  line
  line `(xi) establish, maintain and manage halls, residences and hostels for students and to lay down`
  line `conditions for residing in the halls and hostels;`
  line
  line `(xii) supervise, control and regulate the discipline of all categories of employees of the Institute`
  line `and to make arrangements for promoting their health and general welfare;`
  line
  line `(xiii) supervise and regulate the discipline of students and to make arrangements for promoting`
  line `their health, general welfare and cultural and corporate life;`
  line
  line `(xiv) frame Statutes and to alter, modify or rescind the same;`
  line
  line `(xv) deal with any property belonging to or vested in the Institute in such manner as the`
  line `Institute may deem fit for advancing its objects;`
  line
  line `(xvi) receive gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from the Central Government and the State`
  line `Governments and to receive bequests, donations, grants and transfers of movable or immovable`
  line `properties from testators, donors, transferors, alumni, industry or any other person;`
  line
  line `(xvii) borrow money for the purposes of the Institute with or without security of the property of`
  line `the Institute;`
  line
  line `(xviii) integrate new technology in the classroom to encourage student-centric learning`
  line `strategies and the development of an attitude for learning;`
  line
  line `(xix) develop and maintain an information resource centre of print and non-print knowledge`
  line `resources in the field of petroleum sector covering the entire hydrocarbon value chain as well as other`
  line `related areas of energy, science and technology;`
  line
  line `(xx) provide for further education to the working professionals and other employees of the`
  line `Institute in the advanced areas of technology relating to oil, gas, complete hydrocarbon value chain`
  line `and energy;`
  line
  line `(xxi) offering customised programmes that serve the current and ongoing needs of working`
  line `professionals for continuing education at the cutting-edge of petroleum and energy sector at the`
  line `campus of the Institute or at company site;`
  line
  line `(xxii) encouraging industry to sponsor their staff to join the Institute for higher degrees and`
  line `work on problems that interest the sponsoring industry thus helping develop deeper interactions`
  line `and a research environment in the industry;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) fostering the creation of new basic knowledge and applied technology and its active`
  line `transmission to companies for the benefit of the nation and for this purpose establishing an`
  line `Intellectual Property Rights cell to patent the new developments made at the Institute and to license`
  line `them nationally and internationally;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) being proactive in supporting the skill development programmes of the Government of`
  line `India by training people in various related areas by way of certificate and diploma courses at the`
  line `campus of the Institute or at other locations and involving industry in design and conduct of`
  line curricula;
  line
  line `(xxv) giving broad focus to the functioning of the Institute in the area of petroleum and petroleum`
  line `related technologies under the wide umbrella of energy; and`
  line
  line `(xxvi) doing all such things, not specifically covered above, as may be necessary, incidental or`
  line `conducive to the attainment of all or any of the objects of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (38237)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38237&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board shall be responsible for`
  line `the general superintendence, direction and control of the affairs of the Institute and shall exercise all`
  line `the powers not otherwise provided for by this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, and shall have the`
  line `power to review the acts of the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board shall—`
  line
  line `(a) take decisions on questions of policy relating to the administration and working of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(b) lay down policy regarding the duration of the courses, nomenclature of the degrees and`
  line `other distinctions to be conferred by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) institute courses of study and to lay down standards of proficiency and other academic`
  line `distinctions in respect of the courses offered by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) lay down policy regarding the cadre structure, qualification, the method of recruitment and`
  line `conditions of service of the teaching and research faculty as well as other employees of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(e) guide resource mobilisation of the Institute and to lay down policies for investment;`
  line
  line `(f) consider and approve proposals for taking loans for purposes of the Institute with or without`
  line `security of the property of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(g) frame Statutes and to alter, modify or rescind the same;`
  line
  line `(h) consider and pass resolutions on the annual report, the annual accounts and the budget`
  line `estimates of the Institute for the next financial year as it thinks fit together with a statement of its`
  line `development plans;`
  line
  line `(i) create academic, administrative, technical and other posts and to make appointments thereto`
  line `and to provide avenues for their growth and development;`
  line
  line `(j) examine and approve the development plans of the Institute and the financial implications of`
  line `such plans;`
  line
  line `(k) examine and approve the annual operation and capital budget estimates of Institute for the`
  line `next financial year and to sanction expenditure within the limits of the approved budget;`
  line
  line `(l) receive gifts, grants, bequests, donations or benefactions and transfer of movable or`
  line `immovable properties from the Central Government and the State Governments and from testators,`
  line `donors, or transferors, as the case may be, and to have custody of the funds of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(m) fix, demand and receive fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(n) to sue and defend all legal proceedings on behalf of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(o) do all such things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the attainment of all or`
  line `any of the aforesaid powers.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have the power to appoint such committees as it considers necessary for the`
  line `exercise of its powers and the performance of its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall have the power to establish campus and academic centres at any place within`
  line `or outside India:`
  line
  line `Provided that no campus or academic centre shall be established outside India without the prior`
  line `approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 4, the Board shall not dispose of in any manner,`
  line `any immovable property of the Institute without prior approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board may, through a specific resolution to this effect, delegate any of its powers and`
  line `duties to the President, Director, any officer or any authority of the Institute subject to reserving the`
  line `right to review the action that may be taken under such delegated authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (38238)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Institute to be open to all races, creeds and classes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38238&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Institute shall be open to`
  line `persons of either sex and of whatever race, creed, caste or class, and no test or condition shall be`
  line `imposed as to religious belief or profession in admitting students, appointing teachers or employees or`
  line `in any other connection whatsoever.`
  line
  line `(2) No bequest, donation or transfer of any property shall be accepted by the Institute which in the`
  line `opinion of the Board involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit and object of this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (38239)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Teaching at the Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38239&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `All teaching and other academic activities at the Institute shall be`
  line `conducted by or in the name of the Institute in accordance with the Statutes and the Ordinances made`
  line `in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (38240)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Visitor.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38240&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of India shall be the Visitor of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Visitor may appoint one or more persons to review the work and progress of the Institute`
  line `and to hold inquiries into the affairs thereof and to report thereon in such manner as the Visitor may`
  line direct.
  line
  line `(3) Upon receipt of any such report, the Visitor may take such action and issue such directions as`
  line `he considers necessary in respect of any of the matters dealt with in the report and the Institute shall`
  line `be bound to comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (38241)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Authorities of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38241&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the authorities of the Institute, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the General Council;`
  line
  line `(b) the Board of Governors;`
  line
  line `(c) the Senate; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the`
  line Institute.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (38242)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Constitution of General Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38242&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be constituted, for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, a body to be known as the General Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The General Council shall consist of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Secretary, Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas in the Central Government, ex officio,`
  line `who shall be the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chairman, Indian Oil Corporation Limited, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chairman and Managing Director, Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Limited, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Chairman and Managing Director, Oil and Natural Gas Corporation, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Chairman and Managing Director, Gas Authority of India Limited, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Director General of Hydrocarbons, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) the Principal Advisor (Energy), NITI Aayog, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) the Executive Director, Oil Industry Safety Directorate, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) the Director, Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) the Director, Indian Institute of Chemical Technology, Hyderabad, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(k) the Secretary, Oil Industry Development Board, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(l) the President of the Board, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(m) the Director of the Institute , ex officio; and`
  line
  line `(n) persons, not less than two but not exceeding four, representing the private entities in the`
  line `field of petroleum sector operating in the country, to be nominated by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar of the Institute shall be the ex officio Secretary of the General Council.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson shall have the power to invite any person who is not a member of the General`
  line `Council to attend its meeting but such invitee shall not be entitled to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (38243)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Powers and functions of General Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38243&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `General Council shall have the following powers and functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) review from time to time the broad policies and programmes of the Institute and to suggest`
  line `measures for the improvement, development and expansion of the Institute thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) consider the annual statement of accounts including a balance-sheet together with the audit`
  line `report thereto and the observations of the Board of Governors thereon and to suggest improvements in`
  line `fiscal management of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) review and evaluate overall quality and effectiveness of the Institute and to advise measures`
  line `for improvement of performance and for confidence-building between the Institute and its`
  line stakeholders;
  line
  line `(d) provide credibility, aura, connectivity and contacts for the Institute especially with regard to`
  line `student placement and resource mobilisation;`
  line
  line `(e) advise the Institute and its Board in respect to new cutting edge areas of technology in the`
  line `domain of energy and hydrocarbon development including oil, gas, renewable and non-renewable`
  line `energy, etc., that the Institute needs to pursue, as well as in respect of any other matter referred to`
  line `it by the Board for advice; and`
  line
  line `(f) advise the Institute and its Board in respect of the advanced areas of technology in the field`
  line `of petroleum sector covering the entire hydrocarbon value chain as well as in respect of any other`
  line `matter that may be referred to it for advice by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (38244)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Senate.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38244&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Senate of the Institute shall be the principal academic body and its`
  line `composition shall be such as may be provided by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (38245)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Functions of Senate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38245&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances,`
  line `the Senate shall have the control and general regulation, and be responsible for the maintenance of`
  line `standards of instruction, education and examination in the Institute and shall exercise such other`
  line `powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed upon it by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (38246)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `President of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38246&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President shall ordinarily preside at the meetings of the Board`
  line `and at the Convocations of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the President to ensure that the decisions taken by the Board are`
  line implemented.
  line
  line `(3) The President shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (38247)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title Director.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38247&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director of the Institute shall be appointed by the Central Government in`
  line `such manner and on such terms and conditions as may be provided by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first Director shall be appointed by the Central Government on such terms and`
  line `conditions as it deems fit, for a period not exceeding one year from the date the first Statutes come`
  line `into force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall be the principal academic and executive officer of the Institute and shall be`
  line `responsible for the proper administration and academic performance of the Institute and for imparting of`
  line `instruction and maintenance of discipline therein.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director shall submit annual reports and accounts to the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (38248)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title Registrar.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38248&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar of the Institute shall be appointed in such manner and on such`
  line `terms and conditions as may be provided by the Statutes and shall be the custodian of records, the`
  line `common seal, the funds of the Institute and such other property of the Institute as the Board shall`
  line `commit to his charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall act as the Secretary of the General Council, the Board, the Senate and such`
  line `committees as may be provided by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall be responsible to the Director for the proper discharge of his functions.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act, the Statutes or by the Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (38249)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Powers and duties of other authorities and officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38249&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The powers and duties of authorities`
  line `and officers, other than those hereinbefore mentioned, shall be determined by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (38250)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38250&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the Institute to discharge its`
  line `functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Institute such sums of money and in such manner as it`
  line `may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (38251)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Fund of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38251&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Institute shall maintain a fund to which shall be credited—`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys provided by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys received by the Institute by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions,`
  line `bequests or transfers; and`
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Institute in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys credited to the fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `may be decided by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The fund shall be applied towards meeting the expenses of the Institute including expenses`
  line `incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (38252)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Setting-up of endowment fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38252&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 24, the`
  line `Institute may,—`
  line
  line `(a) set-up an endowment fund and any other fund for a specified purpose; and`
  line
  line `(b) transfer money from its fund to the endowment fund or any other fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (38253)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Budget of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38253&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall prepare, in such form and at such time every year, a`
  line `budget in respect of the financial year next ensuing, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of`
  line `the Institute and shall forward to the Central Government such number of copies thereof as may be`
  line `provided by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (38273)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38273&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Institute shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the balance-sheet, in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Institute shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the`
  line `Institute to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India..`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Institute shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the offices of the`
  line Institute..
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Institute as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (38274)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38274&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall prepare for every year a report of its activities during that`
  line `year and submit the report to the Central Government in such form and on or before such date as may`
  line `be provided by the Statutes and a copy of this report shall be laid before both Houses of Parliament`
  line `within one month of its receipt.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (38255)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Pension, provident fund, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38255&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Institute shall constitute for the benefit of its`
  line `employees, including the Director, such pension, insurance and provident fund scheme as it deems fit,`
  line `in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be provided by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such provident fund has been so constituted, the Central Government may declare`
  line `that the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925) shall apply to such fund as if it were`
  line `a Government provident fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (38256)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Authentication of orders and instruments of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38256&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of the`
  line `Institute shall be authenticated by the Director or any other member authorised by the Institute in this`
  line `behalf and all other instruments shall be authenticated by the signature of the Director or such officers`
  line `as may be authorised by the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (38257)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title Appointment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38257&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `All appointments of the staff of the Institute, except that of the Director shall`
  line `be made in accordance with the procedure laid down in the Statutes,—`
  line
  line `(a) by the Board, if the appointment is made on the academic staff in the post of Assistant Professor`
  line `or above or if the appointment is made on the non-academic staff in any cadre, the maximum of the`
  line `pay scale for which is the same or higher than that of Assistant Professor; and`
  line
  line `(b) by the Director, in any other case.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (38258)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38258&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the formation of departments of teaching and other academic units;`
  line
  line `(b) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(c) the classification of posts, term of office, method of appointment, powers and duties and`
  line `other terms and conditions of service of the officers of the Institute including the President, the`
  line `Director, the Registrar, and such other officers as may be declared as officers of the Institute by the`
  line Statutes;
  line
  line `(d) the classification, the method of appointment and the determination of the terms and`
  line `conditions of service of officers, teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) the reservation of posts for the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other categories`
  line `of persons as may be determined by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) the form in which and the time at which the budget and reports shall be prepared by the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(g) the form of annual report;`
  line
  line `(h) the constitution of pension, insurance and provident funds for the benefit of the officers,`
  line `teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(i) the constitution, powers and duties of the other authorities of the Institute referred to in`
  line `clause (d) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(j) the delegation of powers;`
  line
  line `(k) the code of conduct, disciplinary actions thereto for misconduct including removal from`
  line `service of employees on account of misconduct and the procedure for appeal against the actions of`
  line `an officer or authority of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(l) the conferment of honorary degrees;`
  line
  line `(m) the establishment and maintenance of halls, residences and hostels;`
  line
  line `(n) he authentication of the orders and decisions of the Board; and`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which by this Act is to be, or may be, provided by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (38259)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Statutes how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38259&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes of the Institute shall be framed by the Central`
  line `Government and a copy of the same shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or repeal the`
  line `Statutes in the manner hereafter in this section provided.`
  line
  line `(3) A new Statute or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall require`
  line `the previous approval of the General Council who may assent thereto or withhold assent or remit it to`
  line `the Board for consideration.`
  line
  line `(4) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity`
  line `unless it has been assented to by the General Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (38260)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38260&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the reservation for the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other categories of`
  line persons;
  line
  line `(c) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees, diplomas and certificates of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(d) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree, diploma and certificate`
  line `courses and to the examinations of the Institute and the eligibility conditions for awarding the`
  line same;
  line
  line `(e) the conditions of award of the fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions and manner of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(g) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(h) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(i) the fees to be charged for courses of study at the Institute and for admission to the`
  line examinations;
  line
  line `(j) the conditions of residence of students of the Institute and the levying of the fees for`
  line `residence in the halls and hostels and of other charges; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be, or may be, provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (38261)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Ordinances how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38261&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The First Ordinance of the Institute shall be framed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this section, Ordinances shall be made by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(3) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Board and shall be considered by the`
  line `Board at its next succeeding meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any such Ordinance and such`
  line `Ordinance shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (38262)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Conduct of business by authorities of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38262&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The authorities of the Institute may have`
  line `their own rules of procedure, consistent with the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances`
  line `for the conduct of their own business and that of the committees, if any, appointed by them and not`
  line `provided for by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (38263)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38263&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract between the Institute and any`
  line `of its employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Institute, be`
  line `referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Institute, one member`
  line `nominated by the employee, and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit or proceeding shall lie in any court in respect of any matter which is required by`
  line `sub-section (1) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to arbitrations`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (38264)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Acts and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38264&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Institute or the`
  line `General Council or Board or Senate or any other body set-up under this Act or the Statutes, shall be`
  line `invalid merely by reasons of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution thereof, or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the election, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member`
  line `thereof, or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (38265)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Grant of degrees, etc., by Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38265&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in the University Grants`
  line `Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956) or in any other law for the time being in force, the Institute shall`
  line `have power to grant degrees and other academic distinctions and titles under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (38266)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Sponsored schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38266&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in this Act, whenever the Institute receives`
  line `funds from any Government, the University Grants Commission or any other agency including`
  line `industry sponsoring a research scheme, a consultancy assignment, a teaching programme or a chaired`
  line `professorship or a scholarship, to be executed or endowed at the Institute,—`
  line
  line `(a) the amount received shall be kept by the Institute separately from the fund of the Institute`
  line `and utilised only for the purpose of the scheme; and`
  line
  line `(b) the staff required to execute the same shall be recruited in accordance with the terms and`
  line `conditions stipulated by the sponsoring organisation:`
  line
  line `Provided that any money remaining unutilised under clause (a) shall be transferred to the`
  line `endowment fund created under section 25.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (38267)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Control by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38267&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall carry out such directions as may be`
  line `issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (38268)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Resolution of differences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38268&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `If in, or in connection with, the exercise of its powers and`
  line `discharge of its functions by the Institute under this Act, any dispute or difference arises between the`
  line `Institute and the Central Government, the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (38269)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38269&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions or give such directions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appears to it to be necessary or`
  line `expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of two years from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (38270)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38270&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Board of Governors of the Society functioning as such immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall continue to so function until a new Board is constituted for the`
  line `Institute under this Act, but on the constitution of a new Board under this Act, the members of the`
  line `Board holding office before such constitution shall cease to hold office; and`
  line
  line `(b) until the first Statutes and the Ordinances are made under this Act, the Statutes and the`
  line `Ordinances of the Indian Institute of Petroleum and Energy Society, as in force, immediately`
  line `before the commencement of this Act, shall continue to apply to the Institute insofar as they are`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (38275)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Statutes, Ordinances and notifications to be published in the Official Gazette and to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984&sectionId=38275&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_00011_201803_1523880255984
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Statute and every Ordinance made or notification issued under`
  line `this Act shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Statute and every Ordinance made or notification issued under this Act shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions,`
  line `and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions`
  line `aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the Statute, Ordinance or notification or`
  line `both Houses agree that the Statute, Ordinance or notification should not be made or issued, the`
  line `Statute, Ordinance or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that Statute, Ordinance or notification.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make the Statutes, Ordinances or notifications shall include the power to give`
  line `retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the Statutes,`
  line `Ordinances, notifications or any of them but no retrospective effect shall be given to any Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or notification so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person to whom such`
  line `Statute, Ordinance or notification may be applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
